President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for various judicial positions. John B. Nalbandian of Kentucky has been nominated to serve as a Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit. Joseph L. Falvey, Jr. of Michigan has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims. Alan D. Albright of Texas has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Texas. Susan Brnovich of Arizona has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of Arizona. J. Campbell Barker of Texas has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas. Courtney Dunbar Jones of Virginia has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. Tax Court. Jeremy D. Kernodle of Texas has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas. Dominic W. Lanza of Arizona has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of Arizona. Maureen K. Ohlhausen of Virginia has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. Court of Federal Claims. Robert R. Summerhays of Louisiana has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Louisiana. Michael J. Truncale of Texas has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Texas. Wendy Vitter of Louisiana has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Louisiana.